The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Davis Cup
                                                   Davis Cup
                      
	London: Defending champions Spain, even without Rafael Nadal in their line-up, will be a tough test for Israel in the semi-final of the Davis Cup.         
	Both Nadal and Fernando Verdasco have pulled out of Spains team for the best-of-five series that starts Friday in Torre Pacheco, because of injuries.         
	Top-ranked Roger Federer, however, is expected to be in action against Italy. Federer said he was ready to get back on court to help his team reach next years World Group.         
	The other semi-final, in which Croatia are pitted against the Czech Republic in Porec on indoor clay, has three top-20 players in the line-up. (AP)                                                                                                                       
